 the reserved pea and asparagus mixture over half of the omelette and top with half of the reserved cheese (optional). Fold omelette over to encase filling and cook for a further 1-2 minutes or until cooked through. Transfer onto a serving plate and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Repeat with remaining half of the omelette and filling mixtures."},{"content":"Garnish with coriander before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can use frozen peas in this recipe, simply thaw before using in step 4.","To make this recipe dairy free, omit cheese.","Eggs are a source of both protein and vitamin B12."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","20m","2 portions"]}